<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>:cross:</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span><code>ACTIVE</=
code>&nbsp; , <code>ACTIVE_AND_INACTIVE</code>&nbsp;</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">&=
nbsp;"ACTIVE" will fetch accounts which are active only. <br><br>
 "ACTIVE_AND_INACTIVE " will fetch account swhich are Active and Inactive b=
oth. <br><br>
 If caller is not passing this query parameter then default option of <span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">ACTIVE_AND_INACTIVE </span>assumed downstr=
eam</span></p></td>
