<h1 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-Capability:RetrievingAccountListfromPDP(Nov202=
5ERM)"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability:<span cla=
ss=3D"fabric-text-color-mark"> Retrieving Account List from PDP(Nov 2025 ER=
M)</span></strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-GET/accountList"><span style=3D"font-size: 20.=
0px;letter-spacing: -0.008em;">GET /</span><span style=3D"font-size: 20.0px=
;letter-spacing: -0.008em;">accountList</span></h2>
<p>This endpoint retrieves all accounts from PDP(Entitlements) that the use=
r is entitled to view. And if an account group id is supplied, the endpoint=
 will retrieve all accounts from PDP(Entitlements) the user is entitled to =
view for the supplied account ID. <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><=
strong>Note: </strong></u>This endpoint will only query PDP to retrieve the=
 account list as held in entitlements and will not make any call to the Wes=
tpac One Core Arrangements CAP API to retrieve the details from either 10x/=
Atlas or GCM.</span></p>
<p>This endpoint will be called in the following flows,</p>
<ul>
<li>BR.03 requirement in this SD: <a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=
=3D2041141342#SD:Upliftmaximumloadsizefordifferentlistings&amp;warnuserwhen=
morerecordsareavailable-SolutionOverview">SD : Uplift maximum load size for=
 different listings &amp; warn user when more records are available#Solutio=
nOverview</a></li>
<li>Statements <span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>- A=
ccount statements &amp; Annual interest statements as part of divisions fea=
ture, the associated SD can be found here: <a href=3D"https://confluence.sr=
v.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D2117707286#SD:SubOrgs(Divis=
ions)Channels-Statements-Accountstatements&amp;Annualintereststatements" re=
l=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - Statements-Accountstateme=
nts&amp;Annualintereststatements</a></span></li>
<li><s>Search filters for Account List: <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/SD+%3A+Sea=
rch+capabilities+for+customer+portal+lists#SD:Searchcapabilitiesforcustomer=
portallists-AccountsList">SD : Search capabilities for customer portal list=
s#AccountsList</a></s></li>
<li><p><s>Search filters for Interest and tax summary list: &nbsp;<a href=
=3D"/display/ARTC/SD+%3A+Search+capabilities+for+customer+portal+lists#SD:S=
earchcapabilitiesforcustomerportallists-Interestandtaxsummarylist">SD : Sea=
rch capabilities for customer portal lists#Interestandtaxsummarylist</a></s=
></p></li>
</ul>
