<h3 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-DownstreamAPIInfo(Feb2026ERMdivisionschanges).=
1">Downstream API Info(Feb 2026 ERM divisions changes)</h3>
<p>If the divisionId is supplied as part of the request, the&nbsp;<code>Get=
AccountIdsFromPdpQueryResult</code><span>&nbsp;</span>API request should in=
clude the divisionId to ensure PDP will query and return the accountIDs ass=
ociated with the supplied division and&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43=
,77);">if<span>&nbsp;</span></span><code>divisionId</code><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>is not provided in the request body=
, the endpoint will follow the existing logic</span>.</p>
<ul>
<li>PDPQueryAPI to be uplifted:<span>&nbsp;</span><code>GetAccountIdsFromPd=
pQueryResult</code></li>
<li>PDPQueryAPI Request:</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom">
<b class=3D"code-title"></b><span class=3D"collapse-source expand-control" =
style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</sp=
an><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand source</span></span><span cla=
ss=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Midnight; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Midnig=
ht">{
    "query": [
        {
            "attribute": "RequestAttributes.AccountId"
        }
    ],
    "context": {
        "action": "QUERY",
        "attributes": {
            "RequestAttributes.CustomerUserId": "07a975e0-0a90-4e1c-96d1-c2=
a1e5dcc5a2",
            "RequestAttributes.OrganisationId": "32896172",
            "RequestAttributes.ScopeId": "a39d00a7-8710-4333-adbf-bb82e8c7c=
afg",
            "RequestAttributes.DivisionId": "a39d00a7-8710-4333-adbf-bb82e8=
c9bacf",
            "RequestAttributes.RequestAction": "VIEW_ACCOUNT"
        }
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>PDPQueryAPI response: There will be no change in the response payload, =
PDP will continue to return the same response payload as earlier.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-Capability:Searchforalistofarrangements(Feb202=
6ERM)"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability: Search f=
or a list of arrangements(Feb 2026 ERM)</strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-POST/arrangementList">POST /arrangementList</h=
2>
<p>This endpoint retrieves the arrangements details for the list of Account=
IDs supplied as part of the request body. This end point is required as par=
t of <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>Feb</strong><strong> 2026=
 ERM</strong></span> to support search capabilities as per the SD here: <a =
href=3D"/display/ARTC/SD+%3A+Search+capabilities+for+customer+portal+lists#=
SD:Searchcapabilitiesforcustomerportallists-SolutionOverview.1">SD : Search=
 capabilities for customer portal lists#SolutionOverview.1</a></p>
<p>The endpoint will not query PDP(as the account IDs will already be suppl=
ied as part of the request body) and will directly consume getArrangements =
endpoint exposed from Westpac One Core Arrangements CAP API(<a href=3D"http=
s://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-inst=
l-arrngmntsvcng-v1?tab=3Dcontract#tag/getArrangements/operation/getArrangem=
ents" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://mesh.westpac.com.au/=
components/apis/cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1?tab=
=3Dcontract#tag/getArrangements/operation/getArrangements</a>).&nbsp;</p>
<p><br></p>
