<h1 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-Capability:Getthetransactiondetails"><span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability: Get the transaction deta=
ils</strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-POST/transactionDetails">POST /transactionDeta=
ils</h2>
<p>This endpoint retrieves the details of the provided transaction.</p>
<p><u><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Feb 2026:</span></strong=
></u><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"> As part of NPP Bulk Payment Transa=
ction details requirement, following changes will come into play(refer to t=
he SD here for details: <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/04.+SD%3A+NPP+Bulk+Payment=
s+-+Transaction+Listing+and+Transaction+Details#id-04.SD:NPPBulkPaymentsTra=
nsactionListingandTransactionDetails-03.SD:NPPBulkPaymentsTransactionListin=
gandTransactionDetails-TransactionDetails">04. SD: NPP Bulk Payments - Tran=
saction Listing and Transaction Details#03.SD:NPPBulkPaymentsTransactionLis=
tingandTransactionDetails-TransactionDetails</a>),</span></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span data-teams=3D"true">For a NPP =
Bulk reverse payment transaction, transactionId(<span style=3D"color: rgb(0=
,51,102);">transactionTraceIdentification) should be displayed on the UI.&n=
bsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"> So to meet to the same, Westpac One=
 Core Arrangements retrieveTransactionDetails CAP API will expose a new res=
ponse attribute called transactionTraceIdentification under "data.paymentDe=
tails.<span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">creditTransferTransactionInform=
ation</span>" object and the same will be mapped in the Exp API and returne=
d to the UI as transactionTraceIdentification as part of the Exp API respon=
se.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">The UI is expected to display the to=
tal no of transactions in the transaction details page for NPP Bulk debit i=
nstruction transaction. So a new response attribute called numberOfTransact=
ions will be exposed from the Exp API to meet to this requirement</span></l=
i>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
