<h1 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-Capability:GetDetailsofanArrangement"><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability: Get Details of an Arran=
gement&nbsp;</strong></span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-POST/arrangementDetails">POST /arrangementDeta=
ils</h2>
<p>This endpoint retrieves the details of the account provided in request b=
ody.</p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge">AUG26</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As part of AUG 26 redirections will be set up in 10x for credit and debi=
t interest redirections, and configurations will be returned in the "Accoun=
tLinks" payload. ENUM accountLinks[].type to include extra values for <span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Credit and Debit redirections. <strong>(val=
ues to be confirmed)</strong></span></p>
<p>Possibly values would be "<span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>C=
REDIT_INTEREST_APPLICATION</strong></span>" (Credit interest redirection), =
"<span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>DEBIT_INTEREST_APPLICATION</s=
trong></span>" (Debit interest redirection), <span style=3D"letter-spacing:=
 0.0px;">"</span><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><strong>FEE_APPLICA=
TION</strong>" (Fees redirection)</span></p>
<p>The EXP API should&nbsp;mask any account number under accountLinks[] bef=
ore returning the response if the source / target account is not the curren=
t account. (display only last 3 digits of account number).</p>
<p>UI will display the accountLinks in the "Interest and tab summary" Tab i=
f type is Credit / debit redirection and the current account is the source =
account.&nbsp;</p>
<p>UI will display the accountLinks in the "Account detail" tab if type is =
Credit / debit redirection and the current account is the target account, o=
r if the type is Fees and the current account is the target account.&nbsp;<=
/p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Detail refers to the SD below:</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?p=
ageId=3D2182705430" rel=3D"nofollow">13. SD: Fees, Interest/Fee Redirection=
s and Customer Refunds - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</=
a></p>
<p><br></p>
<div id=3D"expander-277467048" class=3D"expand-container">
