<h1 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-Capability:Toretrievedivisions&amp;associateda=
ccountGroupsunderanorganisationfortheloggedinuser(Feb2026ERM)"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><strong>Capability: </strong></span><strong st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);letter-spacing: -0.01em;"><span class=3D"fabr=
ic-text-color-mark">To retrieve divisions &amp; associated accountGroups un=
der an organisation for the logged in user&nbsp;</span></strong><strong sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);letter-spacing: -0.01em;">(Feb 2026 ERM)</stro=
ng></h1>
<h2 id=3D"expgalaxyaccountv2-GET/divisionList">GET /divisionList</h2>
<p>This endpoint <span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">retrieves the divisi=
ons and the associated accountGroups for the logged-in user within a given =
organisation. When Channels calls the GetDivisionsFromPdpQuery API with VIE=
W_ACCOUNT as the requestAction, Entitlements will return a combined respons=
e containing both divisionId and its corresponding accountGroup. This elimi=
nates the need for Channels to make separate calls to fetch accountGroups p=
er division when a user selects a division from the dropdown, improving bot=
h performance and user experience.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This endpoint will be used in the =
following sequence flow as part of divisions requirements:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Account List: <a href=3D"https://=
confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D2117707286#SD:=
SubOrgs(Divisions)Channels-AccountList" rel=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divis=
ions) Channels - AccountList</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Interest and tax summary: <a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D21=
17707286#SD:SubOrgs(Divisions)Channels-Interestandtaxsummary" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - Interestandtaxsummary</a></span></li=
>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Statements - Account statements &=
amp; Annual interest statements: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.=
com.au/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D2117707286#SD:SubOrgs(Divisions)Chann=
els-Statements-Accountstatements&amp;Annualintereststatements" rel=3D"nofol=
low">SD: Sub-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - Accountstatements&amp;Annualinteres=
tstatements</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
